news.title: UK's Persimmon offers cautious outlook after beating 2025 sales' expectations
news.para: Persimmon, a British homebuilder, exceeded sales expectations in 2025. The company anticipates moderate growth in 2026. However, Persimmon expresses caution regarding demand, particularly from institutional buyers. Recent mortgage rate reductions offer some relief for private customers.

news.title: China Vanke seeks a further 90-day grace period for $290 million bond: Sources
news.para: China Vanke is making headlines as it seeks a 90-day reprieve on a 2 billion yuan bond repayment. Bondholders will soon cast their votes on fresh proposals amid this pivotal moment.

news.title: 2025 was decent, but end-user demand softened as prices jumped: Parveen Jain, president, NAREDCO National
news.para: In India, the housing sector is currently facing a wave of price hikes attributed to climbing land and construction costs. This surge is making it tough for many buyers to enter the market. Consequently, developers are pondering a return to mid-range housing as the appetite for luxury homes levels off.

news.title: Builders seek EDC relief, higher affordable housing prices from Haryana government
news.para: Haryana's real estate developers have taken the initiative to submit an in-depth set of policy suggestions to the state government, designed to kickstart the economy. Their proposals focus on reinvigorating halted projects, alleviating regulatory burdens, and making housing more accessible to the public.

news.title: Tushar Infra Developers & Pantheon Buildcon sell property in Mumbai for ₹559.25 crore
news.para: Tushar Infra Developers and Pantheon Buildcon have sold a commercial property in Chandivali, Mumbai. The deal for the Balaji IT Park property is valued at ₹559.25 crore. The property has a built-up area of approximately 30,195 square meters.

news.title: Tidco sets up model houses for villagers under Parandur airport resettlement plan
news.para: Tidco has built model houses for families to be relocated for the proposed Parandur greenfield airport in Kancheepuram district. Villagers can choose from different designs of 400 sqft houses, with options for cash compensation or alternative housing sites. The state government has also released a relief package for affected residents.

news.title: Anant Nagar plot registration till January 16: Lucknow development body
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority has extended the online registration deadline for 637 residential plots in the Anant Nagar housing scheme to January 16 due to overwhelming public interest. This decision follows a strong response to the scheme, which is being developed over 785 acres and includes plans for parks and an Edutech City.

news.title: Property Share files for ₹244-crore IPO of third SM REIT scheme
news.para: Property Share Investment Trust has filed draft IPO papers for PropShare Celestia. The issue size is up to Rs 244.65 crore. Investors gain access to a Grade A+ asset in Ahmedabad.

news.title: JP Morgan leases 2.71 lakh sq ft office space from Cowrks in Mumbai at ₹9 crore monthly rent
news.para: JP Morgan has secured 2.72 lakh sq ft office space in Powai, Mumbai. This deal with Cowrks begins in April. The monthly rent is set at Rs 9.23 crore. The lease agreement spans 60 months. Rent will increase by 5 percent annually.

news.title: Honeywell leases four lakh sq ft office space at Ecoworld in Bengaluru
news.para: Honeywell Technology Solutions Lab has leased a significant office space in Bengaluru. The technology firm will occupy 399,220 square feet at  Ecoworld. This lease begins in January 2026 and spans seven years. The deal includes an expansion option for more space. This transaction highlights strong demand for quality office spaces in Bengaluru's tech corridor.

news.title: ED files final report against ex-MD of Jaypee Infratech in 'fraud' case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has issued a chargesheet against Manoj Gaur, the former managing director of Jaypee Infratech. Gaur is embroiled in Rs 14,599 crore scandal, accused of misleading homebuyers by diverting funds intended for construction.

news.title: Suraksha Group completes construction of 5,989 units spread across 63 towers
news.para: Suraksha Group has finished building 5,989 homes in JIL Wish Town. Occupancy certificates are now secured for 31 towers. Applications for occupancy certificates have been submitted for another 32 towers. Construction continues on the remaining towers.

news.title: Anarock launches project management & engineering services
news.para: Anarock is charting new territories with the unveiling of its project management and engineering services division. This venture is set to rake in over 125 crore rupees by FY 2026-27, paving the way for a target of 300 crore rupees by FY28.

news.title: Bhumika Realty raises ₹170 crore from Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC & BGO for Faridabad project
news.para: Bhumika Realty has secured ₹170 crore in funding, courtesy of the joint venture between Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC and BGO’s real estate credit platform. This investment will propel the construction of mixed-use development in Faridabad.

news.title: ASK Property Fund invests ₹340 crore in Mantra Group’s residential projects across Mumbai and Pune
news.para: ASK Property Fund has allocated ₹340 crore to bolster three residential ventures spearheaded by Mantra Group. This capital infusion will facilitate Mantra Group's acquisition of two projects via the NCLT route.

news.title: Now, Karnataka Housing Board plans 593-acre project near Foxconn hub; farmers miffed
news.para: Karnataka Housing Board is acquiring 593 acres near Devanahalli for a major housing project, driven by rapid industrial growth and rising residential demand. Landowners will receive 50% of developed land instead of monetary compensation. The move aims to address housing needs in the burgeoning industrial hub, though local farmers express concerns about losing fertile land.

news.title: Land crunch, competition drive strategic acquisitions via bankruptcy process
news.para: Companies are using the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code to acquire prime urban land in India. This process offers clear titles and approvals, reducing risks for developers. Major conglomerates like Adani Enterprises are actively acquiring land banks through this route. Several high-profile transactions in Mumbai and other cities highlight this growing trend.

news.title: Union minister suggests concessions for precast, steel construction to curb pollution
news.para: In an effort to promote cleaner construction practices, Union minister Piyush Goyal has urged for incentives aimed at precast and steel construction methods. He argued that such strategies would help mitigate dust pollution emanating from construction zones.

news.title: Signature Global's sales bookings fall 27% to ₹2,020 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Signature Global informed that it has sold 408 units during the October-December period of this fiscal year, compared to 1,518 units in the year-ago period.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body mops up revenue of ₹194 crore from sale of properties
news.para: GDA successfully raised Rs 194 crore in its first property auction of the year, with significant revenue generated from land parcels in Madhuban Bapudham. The auction saw properties selling above their base prices, indicating strong developer interest. This comes as revised building bylaws and costing guidelines are expected to boost development and buyer sentiment.
